                <head><hi rendition="#c"><hi rendition="#k">Middle Class Liberalism.</hi></hi></head>
                <p><milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/></p>
                <p>The <hi rendition="#i">Reforme</hi> of the 6th instant, contains an account of
                    the recent Chartist meeting at the Crown and Anchor, of which it speaks in the
                    following terms: —</p>
                <p>“This meeting gives us renewed evidence, with whom the Democracy of France
                    ought to sympathise; whether with the Chartists, those sincere and honest
                    Democrats — or the Whig-Radical — middle classes, who cannot bear to speak of ‘the Charter’ or ‘Universal Suffrage’, but cannot go further than proclaim themselves partisans for the ‘Complete’.”</p>
                <p><hi rendition="#c">* * * *</hi></p>
                <p>The present conduct of the middle classes augurs what we have to expect of them, and how they will fulfil the pledges given at the recent elections.</p>
                <p><hi rendition="#c">* * * *</hi></p>
                <p>Witness the conduct of one of the middle class orators, Dr Epps, a timid patriot,
                    a Reformer in little things, who wishes to conciliate all the world, except the
                    active and energetic advocates of Democracy. Who burns, he says, to liberate the
                    people, but will not let them liberate themselves. A worthy representation of
                    middle class Radicalism.</p>
